title: For Sale/Trade:  A brief observation
postcontent:
I have noticed a lot of complaints about no shows and deals being set up that fall through. We all have our own theories as to where this outbreak branches from. We all agree to it's purpose though, to help disable this particular market place. This action makes us all angry. But what baffles me is this. We have done more damage to this community ourselves than any outside entity could possibly hope to accomplish. This is partially due to just plain price gouging, low ball offering, and illegal flipping ( it IS unlawful to buy a gun with the intention of selling it for profit without holding an FFL). And now we have a saturated market especially with "black guns" because of a huge wave of panic buying. 
 We still have an opportunity to regain this market of honest and fair buyers and sellers. If the few of us left will simply use the flagging system that was put in place to allow us to self-regulate, we can make this the great resource it was almost two years ago. I personally have found other avenues to sell my firearms although I do continue to list mine here in the hopes that I can get a fair price and put a firearm into the hands of a responsible person who will appreciate it versus it just sitting in my safe doing no one any good. And I have not made a purchase or trade stemming from this site in over a year now. I get better purchase prices from the gun stores than I can get here. 
 The other practice that we need to self enforce, and it can only be self enforced in it's truest sense is personal integrity. Just because you saw someone else list the same gun you have above it's true worth doesn't make it ok for you to follow suit. This simply floods the site with, well what we are seeing now. A stagnate pool of overpriced run of the mill guns anybody can buy at their local gun store for less. A little self control will go a long way. And not just with sellers but buyers as well. It's the buyer that fed this behavior from sellers. Every time a buyer pays more than retail or pays retail on a used gun it spurs more people to try to sell their gun for these inflated prices. So all you guys who paid too much for something and complains about this market take a look in the mirror. You are just as much to blame.
 Now I have seen a few guns that fit the category of being worth what someone will pay. Collectors grade guns that are no longer being manufactured. My rant is not directed at you guys. Those are the ads that keep me scrolling through the list. Even when I can't afford them it's a privilege to be able to view the photos and give me the opportunity to research something I didn't know existed before. 
 In closing, what I am asking for is all of us gun owners to show the responsibility and class that we should and need to show the rest of the nation. We have a tremendous burden to be men and women that can show this nation that gun owners are not petty immature red necks with short fuses that can't even get along with ourselves let alone someone who has an opposing viewpoint. Lets make this a community that can have pride in being a part of this instead of a bunch of sharks praying on the unwitting and furthering the mind set of the "Me first, what can you do for ME" generation.
